    "caption": "Ten legs, two claws, and a habit of going sideways.",
    "shortDescription": "Crabs walk sideways because of the way their legs are hinged — forward just isn't an option for them. They use their big front claws for fighting, digging, and cracking open food. Fun fact: A crab's shell doesn't grow with it, so it has to wriggle out of the old one and wait for a soft new one to harden around its bigger body."
